                <h3 class="th-name">Elaborations:</h3>
              <p class="desctop" style="color: black !important;">
    <strong>Project Overview:</strong>  
    Our game platform, <strong>GamePlatform</strong>, is a dynamic and scalable web application that allows users to sign up, log in, and play a variety of games, including <strong>Tic-Tac-Toe (TTT)</strong>, <strong>Rock-Paper-Scissors (RPS)</strong>, and <strong>Rubik’s Cube</strong>. This platform is designed to be easily extendable, allowing us to add as many new games as we want in the future.  
    <br /><br />
    <strong>Key Features:</strong>  
    <ul style="color: black !important;">
        <li>No limit on the number of games that can be integrated, making the platform flexible for continuous expansion.</li>
        <li>Users can provide feedback on their gaming experience, contributing to the ongoing improvement of the system.</li>
    </ul>  
    <br />
    <strong style="color: black !important;">Technologies and Libraries Used:</strong>  
    <ol style="color: black !important;">
        <li style="color: black !important;"><strong>Node.js and Express:</strong>  
            The backend is powered by <em>Node.js</em>, a fast and scalable JavaScript runtime, while <em>Express.js</em> facilitates server creation and API endpoint management.  
            <ul>
                <li >Express’s modularity allows for easy addition of new routes, game logic, and features.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>EJS (Embedded JavaScript):</strong>  
            Used for dynamic HTML rendering, ensuring unique pages and game logic for each new game.
        </li>
        <li><strong>JWT (JSON Web Token):</strong>  
            Handles user authentication and session management securely.  
            <ul>
                <li>A JWT is generated upon login and stored for secure, seamless access.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>MongoDB:</strong>  
            Stores user data, game scores, and feedback.  
            <ul>
                <li>Its flexible, NoSQL structure supports new game data without rigid schema constraints.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Bcrypt:</strong>  
            Hashes and salts user passwords for secure storage.
        </li>
        <li><strong>Moment-timezone:</strong>  
            Manages accurate time tracking for game sessions and feedback, regardless of the user’s time zone.
        </li>
        <li><strong>Cookie-parser:</strong>  
            Parses cookies and manages JWT tokens for smooth session persistence.
        </li>
        <li><strong>3D JavaScript Library:</strong>  
            Provides a visually immersive experience for the Rubik’s Cube game, with interactive 3D elements.
        </li>
    </ol>  
    <br />
    <strong>Scalability and Future Expansion:</strong>  
    The platform’s structure ensures seamless scalability. Future features include:  
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Game Expansion:</strong> Adding puzzle games, trivia, multiplayer games, etc.</li>
        <li><strong>User Experience Customization:</strong> Personalized game options, rankings, and feedback forms.</li>
        <li><strong>Database Flexibility:</strong> MongoDB’s structure allows storage of diverse game data (e.g., game history, player stats).</li>
        <li><strong>Real-time Features:</strong> Minimal adjustments would enable real-time multiplayer modes and leaderboards.</li>
    </ul>  
    <br />
    <strong>Current Project Features:</strong>  
    <ul>
        <li><strong>User Authentication:</strong> Secure sign-up and login with JWT session handling.</li>
        <li><strong>Game Variety:</strong> Includes Tic-Tac-Toe, Rock-Paper-Scissors, and Rubik’s Cube, with flexibility for future games.</li>
        <li><strong>Feedback System:</strong> Users can provide feedback to improve the platform.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Persistence:</strong> MongoDB stores game progress, feedback, and user information.</li>
        <li><strong>Security:</strong> Bcrypt handles password hashing, and JWT ensures secure authentication.</li>
    </ul>  
